<br>
The very concept DAoC has of different non-communicative, non-cooperative realms will make having folks around to guid-group with...difficult at best, unless they are made up of folks from the same realm playing as primary.<br>
<br>
The more I consider this concept the more I think it introduces more problems than solutions.  If someone wants to stick with one character (and some of us will likely want to do that) it essentially means they will be sans Daggers 4 nights a week on the two weeks that are on other servers and we'll dilute our guild-grouping opportunities even further on the other 3 days.  Add to that, the person playing that single character will level ahead of the rest and be unable to group even when that realm *is* realm-of-the-week and they're further isolated.<br>
<br>
Hard to be &quot;part of things&quot; if you can't be part of them.<br>
<br>
